The way to restrain navigation is by the use of angular Guards, I would suggest you start with a [CanActivate guard][1]

```
{
  path: &#39;post/:id&#39;,
  component: PostComponent,
  resolve: {resolver: Resolver}},
  canActivate: [CanActivateId]
}
```

and the Guard can be (for starters just ids which are less then 10 as an example):
```
@Injectable()
class CanActivateId implements CanActivate {
  constructor() {}

  canActivate(
    route: ActivatedRouteSnapshot,
    state: RouterStateSnapshot
  ): Observable&lt;boolean|UrlTree&gt;|Promise&lt;boolean|UrlTree&gt;|boolean|UrlTree {
    return route.params.id &gt; 10;
  }
}
```

  [1]: https://angular.io/api/router/CanActivate

